Interface TapestryCallback

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TapestryUICallback
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference. 

    public interface TapestryCallback
    A callback that handles a TapestryResponse asynchronously. Invoked by TapestryClient.

    • Method Detail

      • receive

        void receive(TapestryResponse response,
           java.lang.Exception exception,
           long millisSinceInvocation)
        Receives the Tapestry response.
        Parameters:
        response - The response from Tapestry
        exception - Any exception thrown if the request fails, otherwise null
        millisSinceInvocation - Time since the request was sent. If a request is sent and the user has no network connection, this time will be as long as it takes for a network connection to be found.
